This paper discusses the statistical analysis of evolutionary and swarm intelligence algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of computational intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of statistical tests, which is related to machine learning and data analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the comparison of algorithms, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of statistical tests also involves data analysis, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper specifically mentions the Competition on single-objective real parameter optimisation of the IEEE Congress on Evolutionary Computation (CEC) 2017, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
